Phylogeny.
The following apomorphies support placement of 

Electrocrania

in the 

Micropterigidae (Kristensen 
1998
)

: 
1
) Presence of ascoid sensillae on the antennae (present in both species, if the ciliation mentioned by Kusnezov is interpreted in that way); 
2
) the swollen pedicel (present in both species); 
3
) the greatly shortened labial palpus (present in both species); 
4
) the absence of spurs on the midtibia (spur formula 0- 
0-4
: present in both species, if the single spur mentioned by Kusnezov is interpreted as bristle, like in 

E. michalskii

).
